Verb + infinite

Stative verbs are verbs that don't describe an action, but a state. Some of these verbs are followed by an infinite (to + verb)
Common stative verbs that can follow by an infinite include: 

appear
expect
forget
hate 
like
love
need
remember
seem
suppose
want

I like to play tennis.

He appears to be busy.

She seems to work hard.

I don't want to leave.

